    {
      "id": "0d2d4416_58b86b0e",
      "file_path": "k6-tests/ncmp/execute-k6-scenarios.sh",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 72,
      "message": "I tried to move them before #62 but I was printing each entry five times in the result table. \n\nBecause, in awk, every bare statement that is not preceded by a pattern (e.g. NR==1, {}) belongs to an implicit pattern that alwasy true. That code is executed at the moment awk starts to process file before any record is read. \n\nIn another word, In awk every ­“pattern { action }” pair is independent, and a record is passed through all the pairs whose pattern is true. That is why for each pattern, the entries repeated 5 times.\n\nTo address this issue, I introduce a funtion to init the row variables.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2025-10-07 13:17:30.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "778b6140_6de664f2",
      "unresolved": false
    },
